articles.description: Elijah Minnie scored 21 points and grabbed 14 rebounds and Eastern Michigan rallied with a 28-4 second-half run to beat Akron 67-58 in Thursday night's Mid-American Conference quarterfinal, defeating the Zips for the first time in six chances in...
articles.headline: E. Michigan beats Akron 67-58, heads to MAC semis

articles.description: The top seed in the Conference USA tournament, Middle Tennessee State, falls to Southern Miss 71-68 in overtime of the quarterfinals.
articles.headline: Southern Miss shocks MTSU in OT

videos.description: Joel Berry II drives baseline, draws three defenders and kicks it out to Cameron Johnson who knocks down a 3 to give the Tar Heels an early lead.
videos.headline: UNC's Johnson sinks corner 3

videos.description: Syracuse's Tyus Battle blows by his defender and dishes to a wide-open Marek Dolezaj who rises up for the two-handed flush.
videos.headline: Dolezaj jams it home for Syracuse

videos.description: North Carolina's Kenny Williams does it all, coming up with a steal on defense and finishing in transition with an easy dunk.
videos.headline: Tar Heels' Williams steals and slams

videos.description: Tar Heels forward Luke Maye gets his defender to bite on a pump fake and sinks his contested jumper in traffic for the hoop and the harm.
videos.headline: Maye hits tough shot through contact

videos.description: North Carolina's Cameron Johnson drives to the hoop, absorbs contact and adjusts mid-air to get his layup to drop, plus the foul.
videos.headline: Johnson double-clutches on and-1 bucket

videos.description: Tar Heels forward Sterling Manley elevates to snare a tough offensive board and rises back up for an emphatic two-handed jam in traffic.
videos.headline: UNC's Manley crashes offensive glass for slam

videos.description: North Carolina's Joel Berry II passes to Cameron Johnson who gives it right back to Berry for the wide-open 3.
videos.headline: Berry swishes home triple

videos.description: Syracuse guard Frank Howard blows past his man and banks the ball high off the backboard to get the hoop and the harm.
videos.headline: Syracuse's Howard bounces ball high off glass for and-1

videos.description: Tar Heels forward Theo Pinson shows off his athleticism, splitting two Syracuse defenders and scoring with a reverse up-and-under lay-in.
videos.headline: UNC's Pinson dazzles with acrobatic layup

videos.description: Syracuse's Tyus Battle drives to the hoop, spins past his defender and hits a runner en route to an impressive and-1 bucket.
videos.headline: Battle spins through contact for tough basket

videos.description: North Carolina's Luke Maye grabs a defensive board and throws a perfect outlet pass to Kenny Williams who finishes the fast break with an and-1 scoop layup.
videos.headline: Maye hits Williams in stride for UNC transition score

videos.description: Coming off of back-to-back losses, UNC's Theo Pinson says the team played "desperate" and picked up "a big-time win."
videos.headline: Pinson: UNC had 'something to prove' in win over Cuse
